
When 12-0 Auburn was left out of January's national championship game, SEC commissioner Mike Slive vowed to do everything in his power to make sure it never happened to one of his teams again. But if No. 1 USC and No. 2 Texas win out, an undefeated SEC champion &mdash; possibly Georgia &mdash; faces the strong possibility of being shut out of the big game for the second straight season. That reality hit home for the SEC on Monday when the first Bowl Championship Series standings were released. 

